    "body": "@lightclient  Thanks for your reply.\r\n\r\nBut I think differently with you.\r\nI think for the block 15537393, there also exists 2 eth as the mining reward.\r\nAnd there is a bug for the etherscan.\r\n\r\nI have get the balance for the miner 0x829bd824b016326a401d083b33d092293333a830.\r\nfor block  15537392, its balance is 0x3da14b0b9deb906a78, which is 1136873784532532226680L.\r\nfor block  15537393, its balance is 0x3f6023464bf1ceef3b, which is 1169072334587521068859L.\r\n\r\nbalance_delta: 32198550054988842179L.\r\n\r\nAnd in the block 15537393ï¼ŒTransfer 30.198550054898867892 ETH From 0x76d312...A08a222D To F2Pool Old(0x829bd824b016326a401d083b33d092293333a830).\r\n\r\nSo, the reward of the miner is 32198550054988842179 / 1000000000000000000.0 - 30.198550054898867892\r\n= 2.000000000089976, which includes the static reward(2ETH) + tx_fee_reward.\r\n\r\nSo, for the block 15537393, there also has 2ETH reward as the PoW static reward.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
